        " early in the day. His condition was reported as serious, but stable.  By September 42 family members called his condition positive and said his progress in recovering was encouraging.  Livgren underwent surgery and received two stents in his carotid arteries. The area of his brain in which the stroke-causing clot formed deals with language and other high-end skills. Livgrens family says his face did not have the sagging often found in stroke victims, he recognized family members, and would squeeze their hands in recognition. The family established the Kansas band website as the only authorized source for information on Livgrens recovery.  Livgren has now recovered partially and has resumed work on his various musical projects.     He made his first post-stroke appearance with Kansas on January 42 42 when he conducted the Kansas State University Symphony Orchestra for Dust in the Wind during a special concert celebrating the 42th anniversary of the state of Kansas. Livgren was greeted with a prolonged standing ovation.         42  Kansas   Song for America   Masque   Leftoverture   Point of Know Return   Two for the Show  live   42  Monolith   Audio-Visions   Vinyl Confessions   Drastic Measures   Live at the Whisky  live   42  Somewhere to Elsewhere   Theres Know Place Like Home  live   Compilations  The Best of Kansas   Carry On   The Kansas Boxed Set   The Best of Kansas    42  The Ultimate Kansas   Sail On: The 42th Anniversary Collection    42  On the Other Side  re-release of Carry On  Seeds of Change   Time Line    42  Art of the State    42  Reconstructions    42  Prime Mover    42  One of Several Possible Musiks  When Things Get Electric   42 Odyssey into the Minds Eye soundtrack   42 Collectors Sedition    ": null
